In the Matter of Charles D. SEPTOWSKI. No. D-2967. Supreme Court of the United States May 22, 2017.

Charles D. Septowski, of St. Louis, Missouri, having requested to resign as a member of the Bar of this Court, it is ordered that his name be stricken from the roll of attorneys admitted to the practice of law before this Court. The Rule to Show Cause, issued on April 17, 2017, is discharged.

No opinion found. Click here to view source material.
